<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q18_v9" title="Q18_v9" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceA</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>En un informe financiero, se indica que la cantidad <m:math><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> invertida en un fondo de riesgo representa el 25 % del capital total <m:math><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math>. ¿Cuál de las siguientes afirmaciones describe correctamente cómo obtener el capital total <m:math><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> a partir de la cantidad invertida <m:math><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> en este caso?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        El capital total C es cuatro veces la cantidad M.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Si <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>%</m:mo><m:mi>de</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Al despejar, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>. Por eso, el capital total es cuatro veces la cantidad invertida.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        El capital total C se obtiene dividiendo la cantidad M por 25.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si se toma un valor concreto, por ejemplo <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>400</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero dividir por 25 da <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, y <m:math><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math> no es el capital total.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        El capital total C se obtiene multiplicando la cantidad M por 25.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces el capital total correcto es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>400</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, porque 100 es el 25 % de 400. En cambio, multiplicar por 25 da <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2&#160;500</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Además, el 25 % de <m:math><m:mn>2&#160;500</m:mn></m:math> es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>2&#160;500</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>625</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, no <m:math><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        El capital total C se obtiene multiplicando la cantidad M por 100 y dividiéndola por 75.
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, el capital total correcto es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>400</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero esta opción entrega <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>75</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>10&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>75</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>400</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math>, que es aproximadamente <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>133,33</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Ese valor no coincide con el capital total.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Interpretar el 25 %</strong></p>
            <p>Decir que la cantidad invertida <m:math><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math> representa el 25 % del capital total <m:math><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> significa que <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Simplificar la fracción</strong></p>
            <p>Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Despejar el capital total</strong></p>
            <p>Si <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mfrac><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces multiplicando ambos lados por 4 resulta <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Es decir, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa A dice exactamente que el capital total <m:math><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> es cuatro veces la cantidad <m:math><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
            <p>Las otras alternativas no coinciden con <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La respuesta correcta es la <strong>opción A</strong>: el capital total <m:math><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> es cuatro veces la cantidad <m:math><m:mi>M</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>